Cilium NetworkPolicy + WireGuard mesh (Tier 3 runtime isolation)
=================================================================

Overview
--------
Tier 3 combines two Cilium-based controls:

1. ``CiliumNetworkPolicy`` -- L3/L4/L7 egress filtering for tessera pods.
   Allows only named FQDNs on approved ports; drops all other egress.

2. WireGuard mesh -- encrypted node-to-node transport for inter-pod traffic.
   Cilium 1.14+ supports WireGuard natively (--enable-wireguard=true on the
   agent). The wg0.conf in this directory is for out-of-band peer configuration
   and testing; production deployments let Cilium manage WireGuard automatically.

Files in this directory
-----------------------
  tessera-cnp.yaml        Reference CiliumNetworkPolicy. Apply with kubectl.
  wg0.conf.example        Sample WireGuard config for a single Tessera mesh peer.

Prerequisites
-------------
- Cilium >= 1.14 installed with FQDN policy and WireGuard support:
    helm install cilium cilium/cilium \
      --set kubeProxyReplacement=strict \
      --set encryption.enabled=true \
      --set encryption.type=wireguard

Applying the NetworkPolicy
--------------------------
  kubectl apply -f tessera-cnp.yaml

Verify enforcement:
  kubectl exec -n tessera <pod> -- curl -m 2 https://example.com
  (should be blocked if example.com is not in the toFQDNs list)

WireGuard mesh
--------------
When Cilium manages WireGuard (recommended), no manual wg0.conf is needed.
The example config is provided for:
  - Out-of-band peer testing without Cilium
  - Debugging the WireGuard key exchange
  - Composing with non-Cilium CNIs

The Python builder tessera.runtime.tetragon.WireGuardConfig produces a
wg0.conf from structured parameters. Use it in automation scripts rather
than editing the example file directly.

Security notes
--------------
- The FQDN policy requires Cilium's DNS proxy. Ensure hubble-relay is running
  so you can inspect resolved FQDNs.
- WireGuard private keys generated by wg genkey must be stored in a Kubernetes
  Secret and mounted as a volume. Never embed them in ConfigMaps or YAML files
  checked into version control.
- Enable Cilium's network policy audit mode first (policyAuditMode=true) in
  a staging environment before enforcing deny rules in production.
